{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_019tb2y6zH3WWJTMcv2abyNS","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me understand the two findings:\n\n**FINDING 1**: When crates.io returns HTTP 200 with malformed/truncated JSON, jq fails silently and returns 1 (version not found), causing CI to proceed to `cargo publish`, which may fail with \"duplicate version\" error. The fix is to validate the JSON is parseable BEFORE the versions[].num lookup.\n\n**FINDING 2**: Tests don't exercise the manifest reader (`resolve_local_version`). Need to add 2 test cases:\n- (a) inline-version crate (fathomdb-embedder-api at 0.6.0)\n\n\n- (b) workspace-inherited crate (any of the other 6 axis-W crates at 0.6.1)\n\nFor the TDD approach, I need to write both test cases before implementing the fixes—the malformed-JSON test should fail at the publish stage, and the manifest-reader tests won't exist yet. Let me examine the Cargo.toml files to see what manifests I'm working with.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":5664,"cache_read_input_tokens":11278,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":5664},"output_tokens":31,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"94ef9a18-efe7-461e-91d9-252b6b93035c","uuid":"360b438f-a1bc-4a4b-a31f-8074e1737ae0","request_id":"req_011CbNQbEv76enhEtxfpKDkv"}
