{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01PhAKJbPfsgPhpcwMXJRxrZ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Done. Here's a summary of what was delivered:\n\n---\n\n## WF-FIX-1 fix-1 complete\n\n### FINDING 1 — Fail-open on malformed JSON (medium) ✅\n\n**File**: `scripts/release/cargo-publish-if-new.sh`, `registry_has_version()`\n\n**Fix**: Added a `jq .` parse-validation step immediately after curl succeeds, before the version lookup. If the body isn't valid JSON → print `'registry returned malformed JSON for <crate>'` to stderr and `return 2`. Same exit code as the existing curl-failure path. Fail-closed.\n\n**TDD RED evidence**: Test 8 failed before the fix — `rc=0`, cargo was invoked (`publish -p fathomdb-broken --token test-token`), proving the fail-open bug.\n\n---\n\n### FINDING 2 — Tests don't exercise the manifest reader (low) ✅\n\n**File**: `scripts/tests/test_cargo_publish_if_new.sh`\n\n**Fix**: Added 3 new tests (7 → 10 total):\n- **Test 8** (malformed JSON): `{bad json` served via mock HTTP → assert exit 2 + \"malformed\" in stderr + no cargo call\n- **Test 9** (inline version): `fathomdb-embedder-api` real manifest (`version = \"0.6.0\"`) → registry has 0.6.0 → skip\n- **Test 10** (workspace version): `fathomdb-engine` real manifest (`version.workspace = true` → 0.6.1) → registry has only 0.6.0/rc.1 → cargo publish\n\nTests 9 and 10 ran GREEN before the helper change, confirming the manifest reader already worked correctly. All 10 tests GREEN after fix."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":241,"cache_read_input_tokens":31121,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":241},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"94ef9a18-efe7-461e-91d9-252b6b93035c","uuid":"7eb5c4c